# app/

This folder contains the Flask application code.

## What belongs here
- Flask app entry point (e.g. `app.py`)
- Route handlers (the functions decorated with `@app.get(...)`, etc.)
- High-level application wiring (registering routes, config, blueprints later)

## What does NOT belong here
- SQL queries (these go in `app/db/`, including functions like `get_user_promo`)
- Full HTML pages duplicated across routes (templates go in `app/templates/`)
- CSS/JS assets (these go in `app/static/`)

## API Endpoints
- **GET /api/users/<int:user_id>/promo**: Retrieves promotional information for a user by ID.

## Typical workflow
When adding a new page:
1) Add a new route in `app.py`
2) Create a matching template in `app/templates/`
3) Add any page-specific JS/CSS in `app/static/` if needed
